cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses post-processing methods for word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and machine learning methods, which are relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are also possible categories.
